title: For Sale:  Beretta PX4 Storm Compact, 9mm, like new, with accessories including Type G conversion kit
postcontent:
For sale is a Like New Beretta Px4 Storm in 9mm.
It has functioned flawlessly since purchased new (original owner here), and has no problems whatsoever. 

It comes with all the original items:
-Px4 Storm Compact, with rotating barrel design
-Original hardshell box
-2 10 round magazines
-unused beretta branded lock
-owners manual and warranty guide

There is currently a rubberized Talon Grip branded Px4 storm custom grip tape installed on the grip. Talon grips are $19, and it was expertly installed. If you want to remove it after purchase, simply peel it off. Talon grips leave no residue when removed. 

Please note this is the COMPACT version. Px4 comes in three sizes, Full Size, Compact and Sub-compact. Subcompact does NOT have the rotating barrel design and is actually thicker than this compact version. This compact DOES have the rotating barrel, and as a result it is the softest recoiling 9mm I have ever fired. This gun has a smooth Double Action first shot (unless manually cocked or slide cocked), then a super crisp single action trigger. A joy to shoot. 

Also for sale, is a brand new, unopened, original Beretta parts conversion kit to covert this Type F Px4 to a Type G. The Type G is not typically available in the USA. Type G has low profile safety levers and slide stop levers. The Type F has more pronounced safety and slide stop, and the safety functions as both a full safety and a decoker. 
This conversion kit will turn the levers into low profile levers (ideal for CC), and also turn the slidemounted safety into a docker only (optional for CC, as thumb safties are a matter of personal preference). There is not need to install this kit, it is just an option as I have it for sale also. Purchased directly from Beretta for $69. 

Price for the Px4 Package: $415
Price for the Type G conversion kit: $30
Price for all: $435

Cash only. Must meet at Johnson's Country Store in Lockport to complete NICS background check paperwork. They are great for transfers and actually only charge the buyer the $10. Other places, if they do it at all, charge $40-60. 

My price is the lowest on armslist for the Compact version.
